The Department of Economics and Business at Universitat Pompeu Fabra (UPF) is advertising a job opening for a full-time position as Data Analyst. The selected candidate will join a team of researchers from UPF, the Institute of Political Economy and Governance (IPEG), and CaixaBank Research to work on a large research project aimed at monitoring and studying the evolution of wage inequality in Spain using data from bank records and other sources. The position is financed by a grant from Fundación la Caixa (project ERACOVID19).

The Position Offers
A competitive salary;
The opportunity to work in a stimulating environment and join a multi-disciplinary research team;
Exciting research challenges and a unique opportunity to study complex phenomena in quasi-real time with rich data;
Excellent opportunities for career building both in academia and in the banking sector;
Supervision and guidance throughout the duration of the contract.
Responsibilities
Data processing: understanding the available information in multiple complex data sources, filtering it, shaping it into a suitable format for subsequent analysis;
Data validation: performing detailed checks on the data, assessing and monitoring the data quality in an autonomous way, although under experts’ supervision and guidance;
Interpretation of the results: visualizing the analysis output, extracting meaningful insights from the data, presenting findings to the rest of the team in a clear and precise way;
Teamwork: cooperating with the rest of the team with a very proactive attitude, responding promptly to requests and petitions, contributing original ideas to the project.
